tbh, I upvoted as soon as I saw the picture, and I saw no reason to change it by the time I reached the end.

The pyrovision thing didn't even occur to me until I saw it mentioned in the comments, but I think saying that this is  progression that I love.

The biggest thing, though, that I think sets this apart from  every character in those games can be respawned infinitely, to the point of it being possible to have multiple simultaneous iterations of the same character, and the characters in question, despite looking like faerie babies in Pyrovision, are in fact all adults. This, on the other hand, is a suckerpunch straight to one of the most visceral parental fears, that you might end up hurting or killing your children without realising it, with the added horror that, afterwards, you will never understand why, leaving you with that gnawing, unabated guilt for the rest of your life.








